  "texts": [
    "We remark that more general theories of code deformations can be found elsewhere in the literature 46,53.",
    "The theory we present is sufficient to describe the state-injection operations of interest.We describe code deformations using the stabilizer formalism 54.",
    "Quantum error-correcting codes can be described with an Abelian subgroup of Pauli operators called the stabilizer group S. The encoded state lies in the common +1 eigenvalue eigenspace of the elements of the stabilizer group.",
    "We call this subspace the code space.",
    "Stabilizer codes also have associated logical operators L that can be generated by a set of mutually anti-commuting pairs X Z, ∈ j jL with 1 ≤ j ≤ k. These Pauli operators commute with the stabilizer group but are not themselves stabilizer operators."
  ],
